## Limitations

The report is limited by the availability of recent and comprehensive studies on judicial decision-making. Some sources may not reflect the latest developments in legal theory or practice. Additionally, the search was constrained to English-language resources, which may exclude relevant perspectives from non-English jurisdictions. The complexity of judicial decision-making means that this report provides only a high-level overview rather than an exhaustive analysis.

